it.emarolab.owloop.descriptor.construction.descriptorExpression

Interface ConceptExpression.Definition

  • All Superinterfaces:

    public static interface ConceptExpression.Definition
extends Concept.Definition<it.emarolab.amor.owlInterface.OWLReferences,org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLClass,it.emarolab.amor.owlInterface.SemanticRestriction>, ConceptExpression
    The Concept.Definition expression for a Descriptor whose ground is OWLClass.

    It specifies how to queryDefinitionConcept() and writeExpressionAxioms() for definition (i.e.: SemanticRestriction) of the ground Class (#getInstance()). All the restrictions managed by this Class are considered to be a unique class definition made by their intersection.
    ATTENTION: the {@link #writeExpressionAxioms()} method implemented by this constructor uses {@link org.semanticweb.owlapi.change.ConvertSuperClassesToEquivalentClass} and {@link org.semanticweb.owlapi.change.ConvertEquivalentClassesToSuperClasses}. It may affect {@link ConceptExpression.Super} or {@link ConceptExpression.Sub} descriptors. Call always this first!!

      • writeExpressionAxioms

        default java.util.List<Axiom.MappingIntent> writeExpressionAxioms()
        Description copied from interface: Axiom.Descriptor
        This method is used to update the ontology with a specific Axiom.EntitySet (or Axiom.ExpressionEntitySet) by synchronizing the OWL representation with the internal state of the descriptor, such that they are equal. It is based on EntitySet#synchroniseTo(EntitySet).
        Specified by:

        Returns:
